branch_sales_summary <- df %>%
  group_by(Branch_Name) %>% #Nhm theo Branch_Name 
  summarise(Total_Revenue = sum(Total, na.rm=TRUE), #Tnh tng doanh thu theo Branch_Name 
            Avg_Quantity = mean(Quantity, na.rm=TRUE), #Tnh trung bnh s lng theo Branch_Name 
            Total_Sales = n(), #Tnh tng giao dch bn ra theo Branch_Name 
            Unique_Products = n_distinct(Product_Name)) %>% # m s lng sn phm khc nhau  bn theo Branch_Name 
  
## a ct Branch_Name thnh index (tn hng) ca data frame kt qu
column_to_rownames(var = "Branch_Name")

r library(cluster) ## 1. Tnh khong cch Gower (d liu nhiu loi bin khc nhau ) - Thng tin: Khong cch Gower l mt php o khong cch dng tnh tng ng gia cc quan st c d liu hn hp(s, phn loi,nh phn)
r gower_dist <- daisy(branch_sales_summary, metric = "gower") ## 2. Phn cm phn cp(Hierarchical Clustering) - Phng php ward.D2 gp cm c ng nht cao.
r cluster_result <- hclust(gower_dist, method = "ward.D2") ## 3. V cy phn cp(th hin cch cc nhm c gp dn theo khong cch)
r plot(cluster_result, labels = rownames(branch_sales_summary)) rect.hclust(cluster_result, k = 4, border = "red") #v khung bao quanh 4 cm
## 4. Ct cy ly nhn cm - cutree() gip bin cy phn cp thnh cm c th d x l v phn tch.
r cluster_labels <- cutree(cluster_result, k = 4) ## 5. Gn nhn cm vo d liu gc ### 5.1 To bng mi cluster_df gm 2 ct (Branch_Name v Cluster)
r cluster_df <- data.frame( Branch_Name = rownames(branch_sales_summary), Cluster = cluster_labels ) ## 5.2 Ni vo df qua ct Branch_Name - Hm left_join(, by = ) ghp hai bng da trn ct chung l Branch_Name.

monthly_sales <- df %>%
  mutate(Date = floor_date(as.Date(Date), "month")) %>% # m bo ct Date  nh dng ngy thng v lm trn v u thng
  group_by(Date) %>%
  summarise(Total_Revenue = sum(Total, na.rm = TRUE), .groups = "drop") %>%

start_month <- month(min(monthly_sales$Date))

               start = c(start_year, start_month),
               frequency = 12) # Tn sut 12 cho d liu hng thng

# V biu  d bo ARIMA
autoplot(forecast_arima) +
  labs(title = "D bo doanh thu hng thng (ARIMA)",
       y = "Doanh thu",
       x = "Thi gian") +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = label_number(big.mark = ".", decimal.mark = ",")) +
  theme_minimal()

fit_ets <- ets(sales_ts)
forecast_ets <- forecast(fit_ets, h = 12)

#Chun b d liu cho m hnh 
inventory_data <- df %>%
  select(Branch_Name,Product_Brand, Quantity, Total)

#Chia tp d liu thnh tp hun luyn v kim tra
set.seed(123)
train_index <- sample(1:nrow(inventory_data),0.7*nrow(inventory_data))
train_data <- inventory_data[train_index,]
test_data <- inventory_data[-train_index,]

#Xy dng m hnh Random Forest 
model_rf <- randomForest(Quantity ~ Branch_Name+Product_Brand+Total, data=train_data,ntree=50)
## Warning in randomForest.default(m, y, ...): The response has five or fewer

library(dplyr)

# To danh sch lu d bo theo tng chi nhnh
forecast_list <- lapply(unique(sales_by_branch$Branch_Name), function(branch) {
  # Lc d liu theo chi nhnh
  branch_data <- sales_by_branch %>% filter(Branch_Name == branch)

  # Chuyn i d liu thnh chui thi gian
  df_ts <- ts(branch_data$Avg_Quantity, frequency = 12)

  # Xy dng m hnh ARIMA
  model_arima <- auto.arima(df_ts)

  # D bo nhu cu trong 6 thng ti
  forecast_values <- forecast(model_arima, h=6)

  # Lu kt qu d bo
  data.frame(Branch_Name = branch, Forecasted_Quantity = forecast_values$mean)
})

# Gp danh sch li thnh bng
forecast_table <- bind_rows(forecast_list)

# Hin th kt qu
print(forecast_table)
